Subject: [PATCH AP-03] vmnet: fix netif_napi_add 4-arg -> 3-arg for kernel >= 6.1

Linux 6.1 removed the `weight` parameter from netif_napi_add(), making it a
3-argument function. VMware's compat_netdevice.h still wraps it with 4
arguments via compat_netif_napi_add(dev, napi, poll, quota). On kernel 6.1+
this causes a compile error:

  error: too many arguments to function 'netif_napi_add'

The fix appends a LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= 6.1.0 guard that undefines the
existing 4-arg macro and redefines it as a 3-arg call, dropping the quota
(weight) parameter which the kernel now ignores entirely.

Source note: VMware Workstation Pro 25H2u1 vmnet-only/compat_netdevice.h is
a simplified file (80 lines) compared to the community 6.16.x overlay. It
still defines compat_netif_napi_add as a 4-arg macro (line 45), so this patch
applies to both source variants. The diff context below targets 25H2u1 sources.

Applied by: _autopatch_napi_add_compat() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  source has old 4-arg compat_netif_napi_add AND not already fixed

---
 vmnet-only/compat_netdevice.h | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vmnet-only/compat_netdevice.h b/vmnet-only/compat_netdevice.h
--- a/vmnet-only/compat_netdevice.h
+++ b/vmnet-only/compat_netdevice.h
@@ -76,4 +76,14 @@
 #define compat_netif_trans_update(d) do { (d)->trans_start = jiffies; } while (0)
 #endif
 
+/* [autopatch] kernel 6.1+ dropped the weight param from netif_napi_add */
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(6, 1, 0)
+#  ifdef compat_netif_napi_add
+#    undef compat_netif_napi_add
+#  endif
+#  define compat_netif_napi_add(dev, napi, poll, quota) \
+       netif_napi_add((dev), (napi), (poll))
+#endif
+
 #endif /* __COMPAT_NETDEVICE_H__ */
